Nigerian Finance Minister Meets Investors in U.S., ThisDay Says

-- B y   E l i s h a   B a l a - G b o g b o
-- 
2011-08-08T08:30:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-08/nigerian-finance-minister-meets-investors-in-u-s-thisday-says.html
Nigerian Finance Minister Ngozi Okonjo-Iweala held talks with  George Soros  and other potential
investors in the U.S. as part of the governmentâ€™s bid to attract
funds to expand the economy and create jobs,  ThisDay  reported.  Okonjo-Iweala also met with Citigroup Inc. Chief Executive
Officer Vikram Pandit and JPMorgan Chase & Co. CEO Jamie Dimon,
the Lagos-based newspaper reported, citing an unidentified
official who attended the meetings.  While investors said they were interested in  Nigeria , they
called for better economic management, greater transparency and
improved rule of law in the West African nation, ThisDay said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
